(
 '<h3>Admin commands</h3>'
 '<ul><li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_subscribe‚çô {email}" to the list to subscribe user with given email. They will be asked for confirmation.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_unsubscribe‚çô {email}" to the list to immediately unsubscribe user with given email.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_listmembers‚çô" to the list to receive a member list with email address, status and join date.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_log‚çô [n] [filter]" to the list to receive recent log entries. The optional filter matches exactly on log level (ERR, WARN, INFO, DBG), category (SYS, SUB, ADM, SMTP, BOUNCE, SEC), or as a free-text substring. Examples: "‚çôcmd_log‚çô" (last 100 lines), "‚çôcmd_log‚çô 200" (last 200 lines), "‚çôcmd_log‚çô ERR" (errors only), "‚çôcmd_log‚çô 50 SYS" (last 50 lines filtered to SYS), "‚çôcmd_log‚çô BOUNCE" (bounce events only).</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_setcfg‚çô" and a JSON object in the body to change configuration settings. Editable fields: log_level (0=ERR 1=WARN 2=INFO 3=DBG), log_console (0/1), ratelimit_window_secs, ratelimit_max, confirm_window_hours, attachments (0/1), attachments_maxbytes, list_name, privacy_url. Example body: {"log_level": 2, "ratelimit_max": 5}. Changes take effect immediately and persist across restarts.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "‚çôcmd_restart‚çô" to restart the Alisia process.</li></ul>'
)
